\cf2 Assuming the request passes through the firewall, the server will then establish a secure Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure (HTTPS) connection using Secure Socket Layer (SSL) or Transport Layer Security (TLS) encryption. HTTPS is a protocol for secure communication over the internet, and SSL/TLS is the technology that provides the encryption and decryption of data transmitted over the internet.\
